      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lora Savchova" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lora Savchova" href="/user/show/3035250-lora-savchova">Lora Savchova</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3035250-lora-savchova?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer145091502" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6673247101211936871">I simply loved this book. I honestly couldn&apos;t put it down. The characters were touching and real, not flawless and perfect but real.<br/>What I hated was being in Emma&apos;s head. Not the writing hate, I just loved the story, but rather the existantial hate. I don&apos;t want to think of child abuse, that&apos;s just one of the most horrible things out there. And the worst of it was that, even when she grew up in a loving environment with all luxuries etc., in the end she was still the traumatised little girl who </span>
  <span id="freeText6673247101211936871" style="display:none">I simply loved this book. I honestly couldn't put it down. The characters were touching and real, not flawless and perfect but real.<br />What I hated was being in Emma's head. Not the writing hate, I just loved the story, but rather the existantial hate. I don't want to think of child abuse, that's just one of the most horrible things out there. And the worst of it was that, even when she grew up in a loving environment with all luxuries etc., in the end she was still the traumatised little girl who blamed herself for the weaknesses and craziness of others. It hurt being in her head during the hard periods and I'm sad because out there, there are too many children in the same condition.<br />It's a strong wake-up call for us to help those children and stop future abuse on them. The people who do those kinds of things should be thrown straight into prison.<br />Loved the love story, though. The support, the love, the passion, the deep understanding b/w Emma and Michael was inspiring. <br />Recommend it to everyone.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6673247101211936871" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


