<div id="review_1534219518" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1534219518" />
    <a title="Nancy H" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1555231-nancy-h"><img alt="Nancy H" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1375148744p2/1555231.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1534219518?book_show_action=true">Jul 30, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nancy H" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nancy H" href="/user/show/1555231-nancy-h">Nancy H</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1534219518" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10865395387534484422">This is a classic early Nora Roberts, and is excellent. It tells the story of a woman who was the daughter of a rock store, abused by her mother, rescued by her father, haunted by a tragedy early in her life, and subject to more tragedy as an adult. It is definitely a page-turner and a good read. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

